OL,3,CWhy Summerland remains the forgotten
OL,4,Cdisaster and how it should be
OL,5,Cremembered
OL,7,FBefore filming began, we were acutely
OL,8,Faware of the small number of people
OL,9,Fwho had previously spoken out about
OL,10,Fthe disaster.
OL,12,FSome had spoken publicly, but the
OL,13,Fstory never appeared to reach a wider
OL,14,Faudience in the way that it perhaps
OL,15,Fshould have done.
OL,17,FIf you asked someone on the island
OL,18,Fabout Summerland, they would have
OL,19,Flikely heard about it, but often be
OL,20,Freluctant to talk about it.
