OL,3,CWhy Summerland remains the forgotten
OL,4,Cdisaster and how it should be
OL,5,Cremembered
OL,7,FAll of which highlighted the lived
OL,8,Fexperience of those still suffering
OL,9,Ffrom the fire, half a century later.
OL,11,FIt was Jackie's story that really
OL,12,Falerted people to the shock and scale
OL,13,Fof what happened that night, and after
OL,14,Four 45-minute interview, it became
OL,15,Fclear how silenced she had felt in the
OL,16,Fyears that came before.
OL,18,FUnable to speak out due to that
OL,19,Ffeeling of isolation.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G6/10
