OL,3,CWhy Summerland remains the forgotten
OL,4,Cdisaster and how it should be
OL,5,Cremembered
OL,7,FBut once she had spoken, that relief
OL,8,Fsoon turned to frustration - a sense
OL,9,Fof injustice that had been festering
OL,10,Fin the years that followed.
OL,12,FIt did not take long for a campaign
OL,13,Fgroup to form, calling on the Isle of
OL,14,FMan Government to apologise for any
OL,15,Fgovernance failings at the time of the
OL,16,Fblaze.
OL,18,FAlongside a commitment to
OL,19,Facknowledging that the 'death by
OL,20,Fmisadventure' verdict, given to those
OL,21,Fwho died, was wrong.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G7/10
