OL,3,CWhy Summerland remains the forgotten
OL,4,Cdisaster and how it should be
OL,5,Cremembered
OL,7,FA verdict that implies the individual
OL,8,Fis to blame for their own death,
OL,9,Frelinquishing any responsibility from
OL,10,Fanybody else.
OL,12,FThis was the line that would bring the
OL,13,Fstory into the present day.
OL,15,FThe Post Office scandal, Hillsborough,
OL,16,Fcontaminated blood - all examples
OL,17,Fwhere the blame is taken away from
OL,18,Fthose in control, and placed firmly on
OL,19,Fthe victims.
